> There was a LOOK from WHEELIE.  At this point, WHEELIE'S left optic shot up.
>  GRIMLOCK in the DIPLOMATIC CORPS?  The small MINI-VEHICLE didn't even
> HAVE To say something over to express his look over of incredulity then, just
> gesturing over at BACKSTOP to continue on wtih his story and with an
> expression that WHEELIE did not believe such drek one bit.

<NEW>

BACKSTOP nodded as he saw the look on WHEELIE's face. "Yes, he did
work in the Diplomatic corps." He was about to say something more when
another voice spoke.

"Yes, Grimlock was in the diplomatic corps, like us." The voice was a
deep barritone. There was a strange version of humor in this voice.
"As enforcers."

The voice chuckled, "But the master lost control of his servants, and
we can see the mess he caused, yes now can't we?" There was a pause
"Have you come to rescue your old men, or 'recruit' them once again?"
That word 'recruit' taking on a darker meaning.

BACKSTOP turned in shock!

The voice was that of the TERRORCON leader HUN-GRR! He was approaching
along with the rest of the TERRORCONS!

(TAG)

- Preston
